The paper discusses a database schema for the Accumulo database, which is a non-traditional, relaxed consistency, triple store database. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DB (databases) sub-category. The paper also mentions that the schema has been applied to cyber, bioinformatics, scientific citation, free text, and social media data, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CYBER (cybersecurity and privacy) sub-category. The paper discusses a mathematical framework based on associative arrays, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. The paper also mentions that the schema achieves high ingest rates, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the schema for indexing and querying unique strings in a dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SI (social and information networks) sub-category.
